    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="163"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/17698: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-19">December 19,
                            1941</date>.<lb/>[Received December 19—7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1571. Embassy’s 1530, 12th.<note n="8" xml:id="d163fn8">Not printed; this
                        telegram reported that notes containing declarations of war by the United
                        States against Germany and Italy were delivered at 5 p.m., December 12
                        (740.0011 European War 1939/17451).</note> In note dated December 17 Foreign
                    Office acknowledges Embassy’s communication notifying French Government that a
                    state of war exists between the United States and Germany and states that it is
                    “the decision of the French Government to maintain in the course of this
                    conflict an attitude of neutrality.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leahy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
